My suggestion to use `register` [here](https://github.com/certbot/certbot/pull/7308#discussion_r313650641) was to define an `AugeasParserNode` _implementation_ so that we weren't duplicating the same `ParserNode` code 3 times and use it without resorting to multiple inheritance. This looks something like:
```
class _AugeasParserNode(interfaces.ParserNode):
    def save():
    ....
class AugeasCommentNode(_AugeasParserNode):
    def __init__():
    ....
AugeasCommentNode.register(interfaces.CommentNode)
```
You could also probably have `_AugeasParserNode` inherit from `object` and register it if you prefer.

As for the interfaces modified in this PR, the three real node interfaces are now defined in a way where to implement the class you do not need to defined the `ParserNode` methods which seems like a problem that should be fixed to me instead of making implementations explicitly register themselves with multiple interfaces. I don't think we ever want a `CommentNode` that is not a `ParserNode`.

I think continuing to use inheritance between the interfaces and fixing the `pylint` issue which is a [known bug in `pylint`](https://github.com/PyCQA/pylint/issues/179) is the best approach.

